   <widget class="QTextEdit" name="dedication1">
    <property name="enabled">
     <bool>false</bool>
    </property>
    <property name="geometry">
     <rect>
      <x>570</x>
      <y>120</y>
      <width>401</width>
      <height>581</height>
     </rect>
    </property>
    <property name="styleSheet">
     <string notr="true">
    QTextEdit {
        background: transparent;
        font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;
        font-size: 10pt;
        border: none;
    }
</string>
    </property>
    <property name="html">
     <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;José Rizal&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;'s journey from a young boy in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Calamba&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; to the revered &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;national hero&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt; of the Philippines was shaped by his unwavering commitment to education, reform, and justice. Born in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;1861&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;, Rizal’s early years were marked by a thirst for knowledge, fostered by a supportive family and a keen interest in the world around him. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;With his remarkable intellect, he excelled academically, earning degrees in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;medicine &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;philosophy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;. His passion for social change led him to write influential works that criticized the Spanish colonial regime, making him a symbol of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; font-weight:600; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Filipino nationalism&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:14pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;. Though often misunderstood, Rizal’s commitment to reform, rather than revolution, laid the groundwork for the eventual independence of his homeland.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
